div.div:
A comment is by default a message adressed to somebody, but it could also contain a proposal for a data modification (like a pull request), which will be then moderated by an user or a group before being accepted
A message could be of one of those types :
- msg : a simple message to an user or a group
- proposal : somebody (user or anonym internaut) is proposing a change on a table / a table's cell
- request_to_collab : somebody requesting to be added to the group, or only to be granted the permission to work on a workspace | a table

Each imported or created table from the frontend creates a new Postgresql table to index and store the user's data

A workspace is mainly composed by a list of tables
The workspace object here also contains the UI-UX settings proper to changes from frontend
A git repo (github or gitlab) could be associated with a workspace, in order to commit each change to each table contained within the workspace, so to manage version control, diffs, PR, etc...

Users are entities at the core of the project for a collaborative work around data.
The most important properties associated with an user are :
- permissions
- groups
- own or shared workspaces and tables
Only a registred user can invite someone else to collaborate on an item
